							<div class="post_wrapper author">
								<div id="about_the_author">
									<div class="gravatar"><a href="https://lithub.com/author/jeffschuhrke/"><img src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/jeff-schuhrke-100x100.jpg" width="100" height="100" alt="Jeff Schuhrke" class="avatar avatar-100 wp-user-avatar wp-user-avatar-100 alignnone photo" /></a></div>
									<div class="description author withsidebar">
										<h6><a href="https://lithub.com/author/jeffschuhrke/">Jeff Schuhrke</a></h6>
										Jeff Schuhrke is a labor historian, journalist, union activist, and assistant professor at the Harry Van Arsdale Jr. School of Labor Studies, SUNY Empire State University in New York City. He is a frequent contributor to In <em>These Times</em> and <em>Jacobin</em>, and his scholarship has been published at <em>Diplomatic History</em> and <em>Labor: Studies in Working-Class History</em>. He is the author of <em>Blue Collar Empire: The Untold Story of US Labor's Global Anticommunist Crusade</em>.																			</div>
								</div><br class="clear"/><br/>
